>  hockey stick?) and the transmission under the bus at the FRONT of the 
> Transmission ... is held together by one small screw.  The screw goes 
> through a rubber and metal U-shaped coupling and into a *shallow* 
> indentation in the rod coming out of the tranmission (called the nose 
> cone?).  Well, if you still follow me, this screw disappeared, and thus I 
